    "Based on these hits, diffusion models are appearing as a groundbreaking process for generating high-quality synthetic medical images with improved commitment and diversity.",
    "For instance, studies like [32] and [33] underscore their ability to create realistic images even with limited data availability.",
    "These improvements are incredibly transformative in medical imaging, where the investment and annotation of large, various datasets are resource-intensive and often impracticable.",
    "Diffusion models leverage their ingrained noise-denoising tools to create synthetic images that not only increase existing datasets but also enhance model training robustness.",
